THIRD-PARTY CITATIONS AND DATA SOURCES

This package implements and builds upon methodologies from multiple sources.
Users should cite the appropriate original sources when using these methods:

1. Woodland Carbon Code (WCC)
   - UK Woodland Carbon Code (2021). Carbon Assessment Protocol.
   - Forestry Commission (2018). Carbon Lookup Tables.
   - Uses tariff tables from Rollinson & Evans (1987).

2. Bunce (1968)
   - Bunce, R.G.H. (1968). Biomass and Production of Trees in a Mixed 
     Deciduous Woodland. Journal of Ecology, 56(3), 759-775.

3. BIOMASS Package
   - Rejou-Mechain et al. (2017). Methods in Ecology and Evolution.
   - Chave et al. (2014). Global Change Biology.

4. allodb Package
   - Gonzalez-Akre et al. (2022). Methods in Ecology and Evolution.

5. Carbon Fraction Methods
   - Matthews (1993). Forestry Commission.
   - Thomas & Martin (2012). Forests.
   - IPCC (2006, 2019). IPCC Guidelines.

6. Wood Density Data
   - Zanne et al. (2009). Global Wood Density Database. Dryad.

See citation("TreeCarbon") in R for full BibTeX references.

